    <description>Triggered flow that creates a clone of a won Opportunity when Auto-Renewal conditions are met / Update: Stage: Evaluate with a probability=75% Monthly Cloud=true. Emma 3/3</description>
    <environments>Default</environments>
    <formulas>
        <description>We need to find the position where the number begins on the reversed opportunity name. We can then substract that number to create space for the next number on the new opportunity. //Ceili/JussiK/09.04.2024</description>
        <name>forFindRenewalNameAutoNumberStart</name>
        <dataType>Number</dataType>
        <expression>FIND(&apos; &apos;, {!varOpportunityNameReversed})</expression>
        <scale>0</scale>
    </formulas>
    <formulas>
        <description>Name without the current auto number. forRenewalOpportunityAutoNumber is appended after this in the formula for the new opportunity name (in the Transform element) //Ceili/JussiK/09.04.2024</description>
        <name>forNewNameWithoutAutoNumber</name>
        <dataType>String</dataType>
        <expression>LEFT({!$Record.Name},LEN({!$Record.Name}) - {!forFindRenewalNameAutoNumberStart})</expression>
    </formulas>
    <formulas>
        <description>used to get the possible running auto number from the end of the name so that the renewed Opportunity can have the number + 1. Simplest way to find the number is to reverse the field and find the position of the first &quot; &quot; (space). //Ceili/JussiK/09.04.2024</description>
        <name>forOpportunityNameReversed</name>
        <dataType>String</dataType>
        <expression>REVERSE({!$Record.Name})</expression>
    </formulas>
    <formulas>
        <name>forOpportunityProductEndDate</name>
        <dataType>Date</dataType>
        <expression>DATE(YEAR({!forOpportunityProductStartDate}) + 1, MONTH({!forOpportunityProductStartDate}), DAY({!forOpportunityProductStartDate}))</expression>
    </formulas>
    <formulas>
        <name>forOpportunityProductStartDate</name>
        <dataType>Date</dataType>
        <expression>IF(!ISBLANK({!Loop_Opportunity_Products.License_end_date__c}), {!Loop_Opportunity_Products.License_end_date__c}, null)</expression>
    </formulas>
    <formulas>
        <description>Adds + 1 to the number of the current Opportunity. As the name is reversed in the variable, first we need to reverse it back to the original so that the value will be correct //Ceili/JussiK/09.04.2024</description>
        <name>forRenewalOpportunityAutoNumber</name>
        <dataType>Number</dataType>
        <expression>VALUE(REVERSE(LEFT({!varOpportunityNameReversed}, FIND(&apos; &apos;, {!varOpportunityNameReversed}) -1))) + 1</expression>
        <scale>0</scale>
    </formulas>
